&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate the site-wide calibration and maintenance program; plan, schedule, and track activities (including third-party contractors) to ensure equipment remains validated with minimal impact on manufacturing.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the Commissioning, Qualification, and Validation (CQV) of manufacturing equipment and facility utilities (HVAC, water, and gas systems) in collaboration with the Manufacturing Engineer, System Owners, Contracted Service providers and site QA, applying risk-based strategies and GAMP5 standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Draft and maintain lifecycle documentation, including Engineering Drawings and System descriptions. Assist in the standardization of equipment intake processes and periodic reviews to increase site efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with the Manufacturing team during the installation and modification of new systems, acting as a technical resource for equipment design reviews and technology transfers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor and support the operations of building and clean utilities, including HVAC, mechanical/electrical systems, clean utilities and process gas systems to ensure cleanroom environments and production areas meet performance specifications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor and support the operations of building and clean utilities (HVAC, process gases, electrical/mechanical systems) and act as the System Owner for the Building Management System (BMS), including alarm management.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in regulatory inspection readiness by organizing engineering and validation packages (FDA, EMA, etc.) and acting as a secondary Subject Matter Expert (SME).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Administer the Computerized Maintenance Management System (CMMS) for asset tracking and PM schedules. Manage inventory control for spare parts and gas cylinders, including physical cylinder changeouts under GMP requirements.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Facilitate third-party contractor scheduling for calibrations, repairs, preventive and corrective maintenance, and installations, ensuring compliance with site safety, quality, and Good Documentation Practice (GDP) standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Other duties as assigned.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
